- The integer parameter `grid` must not be null.
- The integer result is the maximum amount of gold that can be collected following the given conditions.
- The maximum amount of gold can be collected by moving one step left, right, up, or down from each cell.
- The maximum amount of gold can only be collected once from each cell.
- Cells with 0 gold cannot be visited.
- The starting and stopping positions for collecting gold can be any cell with gold.
- The grid size `m x n` must be within the constraints of 1 <= m, n <= 15.
- The amount of gold in each cell is between 0 and 100.
- There are at most 25 cells containing gold.